General BEELINE Parser

beeline_parser.Rd

This function provides users with a wrapper function to parse the output files of any BEELINE tool.

beeline_parser(data_folder, name_tool)

Arguments

data_folder

a file path to the BEELINE output folder storing all individual BEELINE tool runs (output folders).
name_tool

name of the individual BEELINE tool for which output shall be imported (see tool collection with beeline_tool_collection).

See also

network_import_genie, network_import_grisli

Author

Sergio Vasquez and Hajk-Georg Drost

Examples

# import BEELINE output file
beeline_out_folder <- system.file('beeline_examples', package = 'edgynode')
beeline_list <- beeline_parser(beeline_out_folder, beeline_tool_collection())
